rComments: Best Prof for financial management, make sure u get him
Kind prof who's accessible outside of class. Very difficult class to do well in though because the quizzes are only out of 15 questions/marks.

Overall a good prof, he really cares about his student and it shows. He teaches the material in a way that makes it somewhat easier to understand. The quizzes and final include a lot more theoretical problems that you would think which sucks since he doesnt really go over those in class. He mainly focuses on calculation problems. Good prof.
Very accommodating during a difficult semester and gives many opportunities to do well in the class. Quizzes and finals are exactly like the practice he gives in the slides and dgds.

Absolute gem. Professor Moneta gave us best 2/4 midterms for 45% which were really easy if you did practice problems. Group case for 10% was challenging but fair! Exam same as midterms. Super considerate with covid and manages to teach this quantitative class miraculously online! Best prof at telfer. You will actually understand, not regurgitate!

Professor Fabio made the online semester so much better. One of the few profs at Telfer who actually cares about his students and genuinely wants them to do well. His lectures are straight up, gives great real-world examples and his quizzes are similar to the practice questions he does. Attend all lectures and dgd's and easy A.

Professor Moneta is an absolute gem. He is super considerate about his students and how they are able to cope up with the course and takes constant feedback on how he can improve his lectures. Skipping class can make it harder to cope with the course but overall he is a great prof
